8.44	Seborrhea	Seborrhoeic dermatitis	Seborrhoeic dermatitis (also seborrheic dermatitis AmE, seborrhea, informally seb derm) (also known as "seborrheic eczema") is an inflammatory skin disorder affecting the scalp, face, and torso. Typically, seborrheic dermatitis presents with scaly, flaky, itchy, and red skin. It particularly affects the sebaceous-gland-rich areas of skin. In adolescents and adults, seborrhoeic dermatitis usually presents as scalp scaling (dandruff) or as mild to marked erythema of the nasolabial fold.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/81/Seborrhoeic_dermatitis.jpg/250px-Seborrhoeic_dermatitis.jpg
